cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.DC, cs.ET, cs.EM

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper introduces a new manycore architecture called Epiphany, which is the main focus of the paper. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper discusses the performance of Epiphany, achieving 50 GFLOPS/W in 28 nm technology, making it suitable for high performance streaming applications. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The architecture is scalable to thousands of cores on a single chip, which is a distributed computing aspect. 
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems): The paper mentions that Epiphany is suitable for real-time embedded systems, which is the main application area of the architecture. 
- cs.EM (Emerging Technologies): The paper introduces a new architecture that is energy-efficient and high-performance, which can be considered an emerging technology.
